radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendiceal tip dilated, measuring 9 mm, with surrounding stranding. The base of the appendix is normal in caliber without surrounding stranding. No evidence for rupture. No free air or free fluid. Included lung bases show no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands are unremarkable. Kidneys enhance symmetrically without hydronephrosis. Normal stomach, large and small bowel with no obstruction. Abdominal aorta and major branches unremarkable. No inguinal or pelvic sidewall lymphadenopathy. No concerning osseous lesions. Grade 2 anterolisthesis of L5 over S1 with bilateral L5 pars defects.
